4:
Our squadron will explore the left
and right paths. You two take the
road straight ahead.
6:
Are you sure we should split up? I
know we're only in the shallows, but
still...
9:
The band of thieves we're chasing
aren't very skilled in combat. Believe
me, we're trying to find them quickly
for THEIR sake, not ours.
14:
So this is the Kaleidoscope... What
an awe-inspiring place...
17:
Sorry to get you wrapped up in this,
Mamnalia. Right in the middle of
your shopping trip too...
21:
Hehe. That's quite all right. I'm
actually rather enjoying myself.
23:
Besides, I cannot ignore someone in
need, even in another world. And
now I know how people help others
here.
27:
Wow... You're super serious about
the whole helping others thing, huh?
31:
Is that how it seems? That's nice to
hear.
34:
...Isn't there something you want to
ask me?
38:
Huh? Uh, I mean, you seem like a
nice person and all, but I—
42:
Hehe, I should have been more
specific. I was asking if you were
curious as to why I'm here observing
you all.
45:
Unfortunately, I don't really have an
answer. I just find you and Stella so
fascinating.
53:
I suppose for the same reason Light
is with you.
56:
Huh? What's Light got to do with
anything?
61:
Hehe, let's just say that both Light
and I love you and Stella very, very
much.
66:
We're going to leave the shallows at
this rate... Just how far down did
they go?
76:
G-g-get us outta here! Please! I beg
of yo—
87:
There... You should be fine as long as
you don't move too much.
89:
Sorry for the hassle, miss. I'll
remember this...
92:
I think we're safe for the time being.
We'll just have to wait until the next
shift...
95:
Oh dear... But I'd like to find
somewhere safe to rest...
98:
This is it, man... We're done for... We
got caught up in one of them damn
shift things... We're gonna die here...
100:
Th-this is all your fault! It was YOUR
bright idea to escape into the
Kaleidoscope!
102: H-how was I suppose to know we'd—
108: Who you think you're talkin' to—
110:
There's no need to raise your voice
like that. We're all safe, and we'll be
back home before you know it.
113: Wh-what are you tryin' to do, lady?!
115:
That's it. Let go of all your fears...
Your pain... I shall deal with them all.
119:
You too, come over here.
There, there...
122:
Much better. Now... We have some
time before the shifts calm down, so
why don't you tell us about
yourselves?
125:
Y-you just wanna sit down and talk?
You've got guts, lady, I'll give you
that...
127:
...Guess you're right, though. The hell
with it. Let's talk.
128: Yeah... And hey, sorry about before.
142: Thank goodness you're both all right!
146:
Light, Nimbus! It's good to see you
two!
151:
The hell are you so happy about?
You were stuck in a shift with a
buncha thieves, weren't you?
155:
Ah, well, they were pretty
well-behaved, thanks to Mamnalia.
158:
W-we made it back! Just like you
said! Oh, thank you... Thank you!
161:
You're very welcome. Now make
sure your friend gets the rest he
needs, okay?
164: Of course! Thank you again, miss!
168:
You scared me a bit, you know that?
Those guys were pretty intense, so I
didn't even think about stepping in
to stop their fight.
172:
Hehe, I suppose most people
wouldn't. But I'm already familiar
with such situations.
176:
And I can only do what I know, just
like everyone else.
179:
That's why I want to know every little
thing about every individual I come
across.
185:
That is my mission, yes... Do you
think me strange?
189:
Your mission, huh...? I guess that
way of thinking is kinda weird to me.
196:
After all, I find you just as strange. I
could never leap into a situation I
know nothing about like you do.
199:
But that just makes me more
curious about you and Stella. I can't
help but want to help you... And I
suspect Light feels the same way.
202:
So in other words, the one thing we
all have in common is that we don't
understand the other side's point of
view.
205:
You see, I actually ended up with a
pretty bad stomach wound once...
Nimbus was really, REALLY mad and—
209:
Oh, dear... No wonder those two are
always so worried.
